          <h2 style="margin-bottom:20px;">Egg & Rice Salad in a Jar</h2>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-5">
                 <h5 style="margin-bottom:10px;">Methods</h5>
           <p> Gently place eggs into a pot of cold water and bring to a simmer over medium heat. Once simmering, allow eggs to cook for 8 minutes for hard-boiled eggs. Using a spoon, remove eggs and place in cold water. Once cool, peel, and set aside.</p>

<p>Prepare rice according to packet instructions.</p>

<p>Allow the edamame to defrost in a bowl.</p>

<p>Divide the ingredients between two jars with lids, and layer in this order: the soy sauce, rice, edamame, spinach and carrots. Top each jar with 1 egg and 1 tablespoon of pumpkin seeds.</p>

<p>TIP: Feel free to swap the edamame for frozen peas.</p>
